UID:10000556-1782414000-1782419400@www.erjcchouston.org
SUMMARY:AI Risks: Scams & Self-Harm with Russell Klein
DESCRIPTION:Powerful AI is now available via websites\, apps and voice assistants. This workshop addresses the gaps between what these system do and the unsafe ways people commonly engage with them. \n\nWeaponization: How AI is used in scams\, impersonation and pressure tactics.\nFake media: Fake images and recordings\, shared by friends and family\, increasingly misrepresents the world we live in.\nExcessive trust: Why trusting advice from an AI chatbot is a bad idea\, and how to do your research more safely.\nMental Health: How AI chatbots and articulate-sounding\, robotic voices are today leading the public to self-harm.\n\nThere is no charge for this tech lecture presented by Russell Klein\, RK Media Services. You must RSVP to register.
URL:https://www.erjcchouston.org/event/ai-risks-scams-self-harm-with-russell-klein/
LOCATION:Herzstein Foundation Multipurpose Room
CATEGORIES:Jewish Life & Learning
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.erjcchouston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Calendar-Event-Banners-for-Website-33.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Judy Weil":MAILTO:jweil@erjcchouston.org
END:VEVENT
